## Payment Structures and Billing Surprises

The payment models for personalized shuttle services contain nuances that often surprise users. What appears as a simple flat rate might involve conditional surcharges, timing modifiers, or vehicle class adjustments that aren't immediately apparent.

After processing hundreds of shuttle invoices, I've identified several common billing surprises. Wait time charges often accrue differently than expected—some services start charging after 15 minutes of free wait time, while others begin immediately upon driver arrival. The definition of "arrival time" itself can vary, with some services timing from when the vehicle parks versus when the driver contacts the passenger.

